<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3713747>
    dc:description "FIGURES 1–7. Reteporella jullieni (Calvet, 1907), lectotype. 1–2. General aspect of the colony. 3. Autozooids in frontal view. 4. Ovicellate zooid. 5. Autozooid with suboral frontal avicularia. 6, 7. Denticulate distal border of the primary orifice." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3713747/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3713749>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Localities where Reteporella jullieni (Calvet, 1907) was collected (in green lectotype and paralectotype localities). Longitudes of sampling stations of the Travailleur and Talisman expeditions were corrected to the Greenwich meridian from the original data (see Ryland, 1969)." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/3713749/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

